    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-12T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-12T02:00:00-05:00" n="1157"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1157">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">841.85/11–1249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-12T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 12, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 12—11:51 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4774. British tanker <hi rend="italic">Louise Moller</hi> arrived Shanghai
                    November 10 from Hong Kong. Master continued course when challenged by Chinese
                    gunboat in Yangtze estuary. Gunboat fired on <hi rend="italic">Moller</hi> with
                    small arms but no casualties. Ship sailed from Shanghai for Hong Kong November
                    12, 0630 hours. Inward cargo 2285 tons Diesel oil consigned Stanvac<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d1157fn5">Standard-Vacuum Oil Co.</note> and Shell Oil. American <hi
                        rend="italic">Flying Cloud</hi> ETD November 13 at 0500 hours.<note n="6"
                        xml:id="d1157fn6">In telegram No. 4786, November 14, 4 p. m., the Consul
                        General reported that the <hi rend="italic">Flying Cloud</hi> sailed from
                        Shanghai on November 13 at 1130 hours local time.</note> Master will attempt
                    run blockade.</p>
                <p>To pass CNO.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McConaughy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
